snippet.textDisplay: Funny enough, I actually did change one of those fuel pumps recently in a 2006 Toyota RAV4. They are only used by Toyota from I believe around 2004-2012 and in a few select models. That goes for the strange filter and strainer setup as well. The entire assembly is odd and also very expensive. The pumps alone can be hundreds of dollars and the filter assembly can double the price. Truly don't understand why Toyota started using them and trying to be different, but they switched back to the industry standard later. A lot of parts on those years of Toyota end up being strangely expensive and uncommon.
